11/07/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Police arrested several members of the Vetevendosje (Self-Determination) movement in Gjilan/Gnjilane on Saturday (July 10th), after they blocked the entrance of the municipal building. The activists were reportedly protesting discussions about the new status of the municipality, under which some villages will be shifted to the Novo Brdo municipality as part of the government's decentralisation plan. (Koha Net, Zeri, MIA - 09/07/10)
